Diagnosis.
MALE. F1 cylindrical, ~ 2 × longer than pedicel. Metacoxa flattened with dense erect pale microsetae (
Fig. 7H
). Penis valves strongly asymmetrical (
Figs 13
E–G). FEMALE. Mesosoma ferruginous-red; humeral carina weakly developed, providing rounded humeral angle (
Fig. 13B
). T2 pale setal spots large, distance between spots slightly less than spot diameter (
Fig. 13B
); T3–4 with pale setal band (
Fig. 13B
); pygidial plate flattened, longitudinally striate anteriorly and micro-reticulate on posterior 1/5 (
Fig. 13I
).

